          <msContents>
            <summary>Dedicated to the Hindu deity Viṣṇu, the manuscript is a devotional work with ritual components, especially focused on the installation of the image in a temple. It is an incomplete copy, covering most of chapter 19 (19.84-19.1048). The incipit of the commentary cites the Devipurāṇa. Manuscript commentary runs parallel above and below the root text. (Måns Broo, Åbo Akademi University, Finland)</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
